verses.verse: The Lord <WH3068> reigns <WH4427>, he is clothed <WH3847> with majesty <WH1348>; the Lord <WH3068> is clothed <WH3847> with strength <WH5797>, with which he has girded <WH247> himself <WH8398>: the world also is stablished <WH3559>, that it cannot be moved <WH4131>.
Your throne <WH3678> is established <WH3559> of old <WH227>: you are from everlasting <WH5769>.
The floods <WH5104> have lifted up <WH5375>, O Lord <WH3068>, the floods <WH5104> have lifted up <WH5375> their voice <WH6963>; the floods <WH5104> lift up <WH5375> their waves <WH1796>.
The Lord <WH3068> on high <WH4791> is mightier <WH117> than the noise <WH6963> of many <WH7227> waters <WH4325>, Yes <WH117>, than the mighty waves <WH4867> of the sea <WH3220>.
Your testimonies <WH5713> are very <WH3966> sure <WH539>: holiness <WH6944> becomes <WH4998> your house <WH1004>, O Lord <WH3068>, for ever <WH753>.
